data.chText: 公司以无比的智慧決定关掉职工食堂。
data.enText: The company in its infinite wisdom decided to close the staff restaurant (= they thought it was a good thing to do, but nobody else agreed) .

data.chText: 无限的事物；无穷尽的事物

simple_means.memory_skill: in 无 + finite 有限的 → 无限的

tr: the unlimited expanse in which everything is located
example: they tested his ability to locate objects in space
the boundless regions of the infinite

tr: having no limits or boundaries in time or space or extent or magnitude
having neither person nor number nor mood (as a participle or gerund or infinitive)

value.def: If you describe something as infinite, you are emphasizing that it is extremely great in amount or degree.

example.ex: With infinite care, John shifted position...
example.tran: 约翰小心翼翼地挪动了位置。

example.ex: His design was infinitely better than anything I could have done.
example.tran: 他的设计比我所能设计出的不知要好上多少倍。

value.def: Something that is infinite has no limit, end, or edge.

example.ex: Obviously, no company has infinite resources.
example.tran: 显然,没有哪个公司的资源是无限的。

posc.def: The infinite is something which is infinite.

example.ex: A centimeter can be infinitely divided into smaller units.
example.tran: 一厘米可以无穷尽地分成更小的单位。

trans: 无限循环；死循环；无限回路；无穷循环；无限循环路
无限的空间；无限航路；无限空间
无穷大电网；无限大容量母线；无限汇流排

partsOfSpeech.dec: af 加强 + fin 结束；范围 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 能不断进入〔别人的〕范围 → 密切关系
con 加强 + fin 结束；范围 + e → 进入〔别人〕范围 → 限制
de 加强 + fin 结束；范围 + e → 确定范围 → 限定
de 加强 + fini〔= fin〕结束；范围 + tive …的 → 能结束的 → 决定性的
fin 结束；范围 + al …的 → 最后的；决定性的
fin 结束；范围 + ale → 结尾；终曲
final 最后的；决定性的 + ist 从事某职业的人 → 决赛选手
final 最后的；决定性的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 终结；定局
fin 结束；范围 + ance 状态，性质，状况 → 资金；财政
fin 结束；范围 + ish 使… → 完成，结束
fin 结束；范围 + ite 有…性质的 → 范围的 → 有限的
in 无 + finite 有限的 → 无限的
